@*
    Plex integration — optional. When set, the catalog uses Plex as the source
    of truth for "is this movie on disk?" since Plex already parses titles
    and years out of filenames more reliably than our regex fallback. Series
    use the DSM folder walk regardless.
*@

<section class="lh-section">
    <h2>Plex (movie ownership)</h2>
    <p class="lh-muted">
        Optional. Configure once and the catalog can tell which movies you
        already have. Without Plex, we fall back to parsing your
        <code>@Form.SynologyMovieDestination</code> folder filenames — works
        for clean scene releases, miss-prone for unusual names.
    </p>
    <p class="lh-muted">
        Token: open Plex web → settings → any item → ⋯ → Get Info → View XML;
        the URL has <code>X-Plex-Token=…</code> at the end. Or
        <a href="https://support.plex.tv/articles/204059436-finding-an-authentication-token-x-plex-token/"
           target="_blank" rel="noopener">see the official guide</a>.
    </p>

    <label class="lh-field">
        <span>Plex base URL</span>
        <InputText @bind-Value="Form.PlexBaseUrl"
                   placeholder="http://192.168.1.50:32400"
                   autocomplete="off" />
    </label>

    <label class="lh-field">
        <span>Plex token (leave blank to keep @(TokenSet ? "current" : "empty"))</span>
        <InputText @bind-Value="Form.PlexToken" type="password" autocomplete="off" />
    </label>
</section>

@code {
    [Parameter, EditorRequired] public SettingsFormModel Form { get; set; } = default!;
    [Parameter] public bool TokenSet { get; set; }
}
